1 ackn owledges by signing a waiver that they are within this period
2 and choosing to deny free services available to them.
3 4. A person seeking to receive compensation for advising,
4 assisting, or consulting with any individual in connection with any
5 veterans' benefits matter must, before rendering any services,
6 memorialize the specific terms under which the amount to be paid
7 will be determined in a written agreement signed by both parties.
8 Compensation must be purely contingent upon an increase in benefits
9 awarded, and if successful, compensation must not exceed five times
10 the amount of the monthly increase in benefits awarded based on the
11 claim. No initial or nonrefundable fee may be charged by a person
12 advising, assisting, or consulting an individual on a veterans'
13 benefits matter.
14 5. No person will guarantee, either directly or by implication,
15 a successful outcome or that any individual is certain to receive
16 specific veterans' benefits or that any individual is certain to
17 receive a specific level, percentage, or amount of veterans'
18 benefits.
19 6. Any person advising, assisting, or consulting on veterans'
20 benefits matters for compensation shall provide the following
21 disclosure at the outset of the business relationship:
22 "This business is not sponsored by, or affiliated with, the
23 United States Department of Veterans Affairs or the
24 Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs, or any other
