1 federally chartered veterans' service organization. Other
2 organizations including, but not limited to, the Oklahoma
3 Department of Veterans Affairs, a local veterans' service
4 organization, and other federally chartered veterans'
5 service organizations may be able to provide you with this
6 service free of charge. Products or services offered by
7 this business are not necessarily endorsed by any of these
8 organizations. You may qualify for other veterans'
9 benefits beyond the benefits for which you are receiving
10 services here."
11 The written disclosure shall appear in at least 12 point font in
12 an easily identifiable place in the person's agreement with the
13 individual seeking services. The individual shall sign the document
14 in which the written disclosure appears to represent understanding
15 of these provisions. The person offering services shall retain a
16 copy of the written disclosure while providing veterans' benefits
17 services for compensation to the individual and for at least one (1)
18 year after the date on which the service relations terminate.
19 7. Businesses advising, assisting, or consulting on veterans'
20 benefits matters for a fee shall abide by the following:
21 a. shall not utilize international call centers or data
22 centers for processing veterans' personal information,
23 b. shall not use a veteran's personal log-in, username,
24 or password information to access that veteran's
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2836 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 medical, financial, or government benefits
2 information, and
3 c. shall ensure that any individual who has access to
4 veterans' medical or financial information undergoes a
5 background check prior to having access to that
6 information. The background check shall be conducted
7 by a reputable source and include identity
8 verification and a criminal records check.
9 C. 1. A violation of the provisions of this section
10 constitutes an unfair, false, misleading, or deceptive act or
11 practice in the conduct of trade or commerce under the Oklahoma
12 Consumer Protection Act.
13 2. Civil penalties shall be in an amount ordered by the
14 district court in an action brought by the Oklahoma Attorney
15 General.
16 3. Each day a violation continues is a separate violation.
17 4. Nothing in this section is to be construed as applying to,
18 limiting, or expanding the requirements imposed on agents,
19 attorneys, or other representatives accredited by the United States
20 Department of Veterans Affairs and regulated by that agency.
21 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
